<h3 id="ordering-and-labelling-items">Ordering and labelling items</h3>
<p>Consider how many items to include in the navigation. Take into account label length and how the navigation overflows or displays responsively. Keep tab labels (link text) as short as possible.</p>
<p>Make sure that the language of the link text reflects the heading of the page that the label links to.</p> 
<p>Decide on the default tab to load. Generally it's best to order items from most to least used, with the most-used item being the first in the list and the one that's open by default. However, you can choose a different order. For example, if there is a chronological or workflow order, the first in the list may not the most useful one to display by default.</p>
